<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-28T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-28T19:00:00-05:00" n="169" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d169">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/631</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW2" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-28T19:00:00-05:00">
                                <hi rend="italic">August 28, 1914, 7 p.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>Your August 22. As the United States did not ratify the Congo Act of
                            February 26, 1885, relative to the neutralization of the colonies lying
                            within the conventional free-trade zone, it cannot be considered a party
                            to this treaty, and therefore is not in a position to take the action in
                            this matter requested by the German Government.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>